 #155)\n\n### Deferred\n\n- #160 — TUI export/import popups (moved to TUI Improvements milestone)\n- #166 — PopupKind enum refactor (moved to TUI Improvements milestone)\n- QR code generation/scanning (deferred to v0.5.1)\n\n---\n\n### Dependency graph\n\n```\n#98 (node fix)\n\n#155 (bundle crate)          #156 (subcommands)\n  |       \\                     |\n  |        \\--------------------|--------\\\n#157 (export)              #158 (import)    #159 (submit API)\n  |                           |\n#161 (integration tests)   #162 (spec doc)\n```\n\n### Submit API changes\n\n`POST /api/v1/submit` migrates to accept bundles:\n```\nBody: [count: u32 LE][frame_len: u32 LE][frame]...[frame_len: u32 LE][frame]\n```\nTransport trait changes: `submit_message(envelope)` → `submit_messages(Vec<envelope>)`. Single-message callers pass `vec![envelope]`.\n\n### CLI commands\n\n```\nreme export [OPTIONS] <FILE>\n  --to <PUBLIC_ID>   Export only messages for this recipient\n  --all              Export all pending (default)\n  --include-sent     Include confirmed messages\n  --force            Overwrite existing file\n\nreme import <FILE>\n```\n\nImport routes messages by `routing_key`: own messages → `Client::process_message()`, others → outbox for relay. Deduplication by `message_id` (idempotent).\n\n### Success criteria (from ROADMAP)\n\n- [ ] Round-trip export → USB → import works correctly\n- [ ] Archive format documented for interoperability\n- [ ] No data loss or corruption in transfer\nOUTER\n)\" 2>&1",
