 Import target | Tombstone handling |\n|--------------|-------------------|\n| **Client** | Process as delivery receipt (update DAG state, confirm delivery) |\n| **Node** | Clear matching mailbox entry (`MailboxStore::apply_tombstone()`) + optionally forward to other connected nodes |\n\nWhen **exporting from a node**, tombstones received since the last export should be included — they need to propagate to other nodes to clear their caches too.\n\nWhen **exporting from a client**, pending tombstones from the ack queue should be included — the relay node needs them to clear its mailbox.\n\n### Practical scope question\n\nThe bundle format and `reme-bundle` crate already support all four flows. The question is how many CLI entry points to build in v0.5:\n\n**Option A: Client-only CLI in v0.5, node CLI in v0.5.1**\n- v0.5: `reme export`, `reme import` (client binary only)\n- Client import already handles \"not for me → relay via outbox\", which covers client→node implicitly (client imports, outbox relays to configured nodes)\n- Node export/import as a fast follow\n\n**Option B: Both CLIs in v0.5**\n- `reme export/import` + `reme-node export/import`\n- Complete sneakernet story from day one\n- More work but the node commands are simpler (no decrypt, no outbox — just mailbox read/write)\n\nThe node commands are actually simpler than the client commands — they just read/write the mailbox store. No decryption, no outbox, no tiered delivery. The `MailboxStore` already has `store_message()` and `get_messages_for_recipient()`.",
